body.note:
The search filter is case insensitive. The following wildcards are accepted:

* - any string;

? - any character;

, - patterns separator.
      If no wildcards are specified, the string to search is used as a partial match (like
        *textToFind*).

body.p:
has a predefined order of the groups in the Outline view:
for location, the names of the files are sorted alphabetically. The main file is the one you are editing and it is located at the top of the list;
for type, the order is: properties, targets, references. When no grouping is available sorts the components depending on their order in the document. also takes into account the name of the file that the components are part of.
